# Shopify Section & Block Development — Horizon Theme

## Section Structure

Always use the capture-children-then-render pattern with `snippets/section.liquid`:

```liquid
{% capture children %}
  {% content_for 'blocks' %}
{% endcapture %}

{% render 'section', section: section, children: children %}
```

For fixed-structure sections with named slots, use typed block references:

```liquid
{% capture media %}
  {% content_for 'block', type: '_media', id: 'static-media' %}
{% endcapture %}
{% capture content %}
  {% content_for 'block', type: '_content', id: 'static-content' %}
{% endcapture %}
```

## Block-First Architecture

- Every piece of merchant-editable content MUST be a block, not hardcoded HTML.
- Use `@theme` and `@app` in the blocks array for theme and app blocks.
- Prefix internal-only blocks (not directly added by merchants) with `_` (e.g. `_card`, `_heading`).
- Use the `group` block type for nested container layouts — it renders via `snippets/group.liquid`.
- Blocks delegate rendering to snippets: `{% render 'text', block: block %}`, `{% render 'button', ... %}`.

## Schema Conventions

### Section Settings Order

Group settings under these headers in this order:

1. `"content": "t:content.layout"` — direction, alignment, gap
2. `"content": "t:content.size"` — section_width, section_height
3. `"content": "t:content.appearance"` — color_scheme, background_media, borders, overlay
4. `"content": "t:content.padding"` — padding-block-start, padding-block-end

### Setting Best Practices

- Use translation keys for all labels: `"label": "t:settings.color_scheme"`
- Use `visible_if` to hide conditional settings: `"visible_if": "{{ section.settings.border != 'none' }}"`
- Keep settings minimal — only expose what the merchant truly needs to customize.
- Prefer `color_scheme` (type: `color_scheme`) over raw color pickers.
- Use `range` for padding (0–100, step 1, unit px) and gap.
- Use `select` for layout choices (direction, alignment, width).
- Use `richtext` for editable content blocks.

### Presets

Always include at least one preset with sensible defaults and a `block_order`:

```json
"presets": [
  {
    "name": "t:names.my_section",
    "category": "t:categories.text",
    "blocks": { ... },
    "block_order": ["heading", "text", "button"],
    "settings": {
      "section_height": "small",
      "padding-block-start": 48,
      "padding-block-end": 48
    }
  }
]
```

## Liquid Best Practices

- Use `{% liquid %}` for multi-line logic (assign, if, for).
- Use `#` comments inside `{% liquid %}` blocks, not HTML comments.
- Use `{% render %}` — never `{% include %}`.
- Scope all variables with `assign` or `capture`.
- Use `{{ 'key' | t }}` for user-facing strings.
- Use `{%- -%}` whitespace-trimming tags where output cleanliness matters.
- For images, use `image_url` + `image_tag` with `widths` and `sizes` attributes.
- Use `placeholder_svg_tag` for empty image states.

## CSS & Styling

- Use `{% stylesheet %}` blocks inside sections for section-specific CSS.
- NEVER use inline hex colors or hardcoded font families — always use CSS variables.
- Apply color schemes via class: `color-{{ section.settings.color_scheme }}`.
- Use existing layout classes: `layout-panel-flex`, `layout-panel-flex--row`, `layout-panel-flex--column`, `spacing-style`, `section--page-width`, `section--full-width`, `mobile-column`.
- Use theme CSS variables for colors (`--color-background`, `--color-foreground`, `--color-primary`), fonts (`--font-body--family`, `--font-heading--family`), spacing (`--margin-*`, `--padding-*`, `--gap-*`), and animation (`--animation-speed`, `--ease-out-cubic`).
- Use BEM-like naming for custom classes: `.my-section`, `.my-section__element`, `.my-section--modifier`.

## Key Snippets to Reuse

| Snippet | Purpose | Usage |
|---------|---------|-------|
| `section` | Full section wrapper (background, layout, overlay) | `{% render 'section', section: section, children: children %}` |
| `group` | Block container with flex layout | `{% render 'group', children: children, settings: block.settings %}` |
| `spacing-style` | Responsive padding CSS vars | `style="{% render 'spacing-style', settings: section.settings %}"` |
| `layout-panel-style` | Flex direction, alignment, gap | `style="{% render 'layout-panel-style', settings: section.settings %}"` |
| `gap-style` | Gap CSS variable | `{% render 'gap-style', value: 12 %}` |
| `size-style` | Width/height CSS vars | `style="{% render 'size-style', settings: block.settings %}"` |
| `border-override` | Border styling | `style="{% render 'border-override', settings: section.settings %}"` |
| `background-media` | Background image/video | `{% render 'background-media', background_media: settings.background_media, ... %}` |
| `overlay` | Section/block overlay | `{% render 'overlay', settings: section.settings, layer: '0' %}` |
| `text` | Text block rendering | `{% render 'text', block: block %}` |
| `button` | Button rendering | `{% render 'button', link: block.settings.link, ... %}` |
| `image` | Image rendering | See `snippets/image.liquid` for params |

## Standard Section Settings Template (Copy-Paste)

```json
"settings": [
  { "type": "header", "content": "t:content.layout" },
  { "type": "select", "id": "content_direction", "label": "t:settings.direction",
    "options": [
      { "value": "column", "label": "t:options.vertical" },
      { "value": "row", "label": "t:options.horizontal" }
    ], "default": "column" },
  { "type": "checkbox", "id": "vertical_on_mobile", "label": "t:settings.vertical_on_mobile", "default": true,
    "visible_if": "{{ section.settings.content_direction == 'row' }}" },
  { "type": "range", "id": "gap", "label": "t:settings.gap", "min": 0, "max": 100, "step": 1, "unit": "px", "default": 12 },
  { "type": "header", "content": "t:content.size" },
  { "type": "select", "id": "section_width", "label": "t:settings.width",
    "options": [
      { "value": "page-width", "label": "t:options.page" },
      { "value": "full-width", "label": "t:options.full" }
    ], "default": "page-width" },
  { "type": "header", "content": "t:content.appearance" },
  { "type": "color_scheme", "id": "color_scheme", "label": "t:settings.color_scheme", "default": "scheme-1" },
  { "type": "header", "content": "t:content.padding" },
  { "type": "range", "id": "padding-block-start", "label": "t:settings.top", "min": 0, "max": 100, "step": 1, "unit": "px", "default": 48 },
  { "type": "range", "id": "padding-block-end", "label": "t:settings.bottom", "min": 0, "max": 100, "step": 1, "unit": "px", "default": 48 }
]
```

## File Naming

- Sections: `sections/my-section.liquid` (kebab-case)
- Blocks: `blocks/my-block.liquid` (kebab-case), `blocks/_internal-block.liquid` (underscore prefix for internal)
- Snippets: `snippets/my-snippet.liquid` (kebab-case)
